@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "SunMaze" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a tile that is occupied by a small square dot
or a mirror (a diagonal shape). If the space has a small dot, a
mirror will appear there. If a mirror is already at that position,
it will either change its orientation or disappear. If the sun's
ray is already at that position, it will continue its way or will
be reflected, according to the mirror's orientation.

  To move, click on one of the arrow tiles located at the edge of
the game board, note that you can also move by using the cursor
keys. You can move anywhere you like, as, contrary to the classic
labyrinth type of game, it is not necessary to follow the alleys.

  The arrival position is represented by a small octagonal shape.
It is 'locked' by a mirror, which can be removed, in order to let
the sun's ray pass through...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

